          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-04-24T16:22:10Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Ending Too Big to Jail Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Emergency Economic Stabilization Act of 2008 to (1)&nbsp;replace the Office of the Special Inspector General for the Troubled&nbsp;Asset Relief Program with&nbsp;the Office of the Special Inspector General for Financial Institution Crime, (2) task the office with investigating crimes within financial institutions and with conducting material-loss reviews when such institutions fail, and (3) otherwise revise provisions related to crime and fraud in financial institutions. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-03-14T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
